\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Installation
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Copy all of the above files (except source.zip) into a single directory on your hard disk, for example, C:\\Calmira.  Avoid putting these in your Windows directory if possible.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 The INI files are constantly modified, so the directory must have write permissions.  If you are using it over a network, you can make Calmira load its settings from the Windows directory.  See the {\uldb Miscellaneous Settings}{\v MiscSettings
} topic for details.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 3D controls library
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Calmira requires the Ctl3dv2.dll module which is supplied in a ZIP file.  If you don't already have this file in your \\Windows\\
System directory, unzip it to there.  Do not leave Ctl3dv2.dll in the same directory as Calmira.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Setting Calmira as the shell
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 If you don't need Program M
anager any more, you can use Calmira as the Windows shell.  You need to modify the System.ini file in your Windows directory, so make a backup copy of it first.  Look for the [Boot] section, where you will find something like:
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 {\f11\fs18 [Boot]
\par shell=progman.exe
\par }\pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 Comment this out by adding a semi-colon in front of it, and add a line pointing to Calmira, for example
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 {\f11\fs18 [Boot]
\par ;shell=progman.exe
\par shell=c:\\calmira\\calmira.exe
\par }\pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 Restart Windows for the new shell to take effect.  If you encounter problems when loading Windows, reset the shell to Program Manager and see the {\uldb Common Problems}{\v CommonProbs} section for more help.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Using the Calmira task manager
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 If you are currently using the default Windows Task Manager, you are recommended to change to the one supplied with Calmira.  To do so, add the following entry to System.ini:
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s20 \f11\fs18\cf1\lang2057 [Boot]
\par \pard \s20 taskman.exe=c:\\calmira\\ctaskman.exe
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
\par \pard \s21 You need to restart Windows for this setting to take effect.  When Calmira is running, double clicking on the desktop or pressing Ctrl+Esc will invoke the new Ta
sk Manager.  If Calmira is not running, then the old Windows Task Manager is loaded instead.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 If Calmira is the shell and it is not running, the Task Manager will ask you if you want to restart Calmira.
\par \pard \s21 
