\par \pard \s21 {\b Start Menu}
\par \pard \s21 Calmira has a new method for selecting intenal icons for standard Start Menu items.  It no longer assigns default icons to macro commands (ie. $find and $run).  Instead, you can select internal icons directly from the \ldblquote Icon from
\ldblquote  dropdown list (ie. <find> and <run>).
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 If you have icons pointing to calmira.exe(x) or w95icons.dll(x) , replace those entries with those from the dropdown list
.  This insures a consistent look for standard icons, wether you have the Start Menu set to display large or small icons.  This method also saves resources because it does not have to load the same icon twice.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 {\b Password encryption}
\par \pard \s21 If you have Multiple Users enabled, you will find you can no longer log on. This is because the password encrytption method has changed.  Instead of saving the password as just hex values, the password is now slightly beter encrypted.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 To reset your passwords, open CALUSERS.INI in notepad and remove the password portion from the user entries.  For example, change:
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s20 \f11\fs18\cf1\lang2057 [Users]
\par \pard \s20 Calmira=E0F6A7B5C
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
\par \pard \s21 to
\par 
\par \pard\plain \s20 \f11\fs18\cf1\lang2057 [Users]
\par \pard \s20 Calmira=
