\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Settings dialogs
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 The computer window is the centre of Calmira, and if you right click between the icons, a popup menu appears,
 which lets you access dialogs to configure the program.  These dialog boxes are often available from other places but you can always open them from here.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 When you right click on the Computer icon, the Start Menu appears (it is normally accessed from the Taskbar).  You can make the Computer's normal popup menu appear instead, through the {\uldb System Properties dialog}{\v SystemProp}.
\par \pard \s21 
\par 
