\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
\par \pard \s21 
When you drop files or folders into the bin icon, they are moved to hidden directories instead of being deleted.  If you change your mind, you can restore them to their original location.  Otherwise, you'll need to empty the bin to free up the space used 
by the files.
\par \pard \s21 
\par Double click on the icon to open the bin window.
\par 
\par \pard \s21\qc \{bmc bin.bmp\}
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 How to restore files
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 After selecting the items, choose Restore from the popup menu to move each file or folder back to where it came from.  Alternatively, drag the items to an icon window or shortcut.  This moves them all to that location.

\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Viewing folders in the bin
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
You can double click on a folder in the bin to show its contents in an icon window.  The binned files are placed in a temporary folder which may have tilde (~) characters and numbers in the name.  In general, you should not modify files and folders that a
re still in the bin, because Calmira may not be able to restore or keep track of them.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 How to empty the bin
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 The popup menu has Delete and Empty commands, which deletes selected items and all trash, respectively.  If you choose {\uldb Properties}{\v BinProp} from the menu, you can configure the bin to clear trash automatically.

\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Using more than one bin directory
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 You can specify which drives to store trash on, and which folders to use.  If you have more than one hard disk drive, this could speed things up because trash from
 each drive can be moved quickly and need not be copied to another disk.
\par \pard \s21 
\par In the [Bin Locations] section, add mappings of drive=folder.  For example:
\par 
\par \pard \s21 {\f11\fs18 [Bin locations]
\par c=c:\\windows\\temp
\par d=d:\\waste
\par f=e:\\trash
\par }\pard \s21 
\par This tells Calmira to store all files from drive F: in the folder e:\\Trash.
\par 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Automatically binning deleted files
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 You can redirect all files deleted from Calmira's icon windows into the bin by selecting the "Move objects into bin instead of deleting" option from the {\uldb File System Properties dialog}{\v FileSystemProp}
.  When you press Del from an icon window, the effect is the same as dropping the objects into the bin icon.
\par \pard \s21 When you choose this option and want to properly delete a file, press Shift+Del instead, or hold down shift when choosing Delete from the popup menu.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 
This setting does not affect files deleted by other programs, or from the Find Files dialog or Explorer tree.  You must manually clear out the bin to free up disk space, but remember that files could be stored on different drives so you need to ch
eck the[Bin locations] section if you need more space on a particular disk.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 How to hide the bin
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Set its caption to an empty string, and restart Calmira.
\par \pard \s21 
