\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
\par This dialog contains global, screen display and network settings.  Open it from the {\uldb Computer}{\v Computer} window by right clicking between the icons and choosing Properties at the top of the menu.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Play system sounds when displaying messages
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 The sound files are the ones that you choose from Control Panel.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Display page colours
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
Some of the "colour" names are actually Windows screen elements.  Use these "colours" to match Calmira's colour scheme to your current Windows colour scheme.  For example, assign the BtnFace colour to something which should alw
ays stay the same colour as Windows buttons.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Advanced settings
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
The Advanced page contains an INI file editor that lets you modify Calmira's configuration file without the need to quit Calmira or use a separate text editor.  Double click on a section name or click on a book icon to show the settings it contains.  Thei
dentifiers on the left are not case sensitive, but the values on the right {\i are}.  The order in which lines appear does not usually matter.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 Many of the INI file settings can be adjusted through various dialog boxes, and these should be left alone.  You should also leave settings that are updated automatically, such as window positions.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 {\b Users page}
\par \pard \s21 On the Users page, you can create different User Profiles for Calmira. Each user will have it\rquote s own Calmira settings. The user\rquote s profile is stored in the user\rquote s own \ldblquote profile/[username]\rdblquote 
 directory, placed under the Calmira home directory. The first time a new user logs in at start up, Calmira copies all the general settings from the Calmira home directory to the user\rquote s newly created directory.
\par \pard \s21 {\b 
\par }{\b\cf2 Note:} Some settings will not take effect until you restart the program.
\par \pard \s21 
