\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
\par Open this dialog from the {\uldb Explorer Tree}{\v Explorer} by selecting a disk and choosing Properties from the popup menu. You will see imformation about that disk\rquote s size, used and free space, drive type and volume label.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 {\b Changing the volume label}
\par \pard \s21 Click on the volume label edit box and edit the name. You can use up to 11 characters. Press ENTER to write the new label to the disk.
\par \pard \s21 
