 by selecting one or more objects, and choosing Properties from the objects' popup menu.  You will receive different information depending on whether you selected a file, a folder or multiple items.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 File attributes
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 If you select multiple items, some check boxes may be greyed, which indicates that items differ in this attribute.  Leave a check box greyed to prevent the particular attribute from being modified.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Associating programs
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 When type in your own command to run, you need to include %1 on the command line where the document filename should be inserted.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Version information
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Under Windows 3.1, only version information compiled by a Microsoft resource compiler can be reliably detected.
\par \pard \s21 
\par 
\par \pard\plain \s18\keepn \b\f5\cf2\lang2057 \page {\cs15\f6\fs16\up6 #{\footnote \pard\plain \s16 \f6\fs20\lang2057 {\cs15\fs16\up6 #} FileSystemProp}} {\cs15\f6\fs16\up6 ${\footnote \pard\plain \s16 \f6\fs20\lang2057 {\cs15\fs16\up6 $}
