\pard\plain \s16 \f6\fs20\lang2057 {\cs15\fs16\up6 +} 00000}} File System properties dialog
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
\par This dialog controls the built-in file manager.  To open it, choose File System from an {\uldb icon window's}{\v IconWindows} popup menu, or open it via the {\uldb Computer}{\v Computer} window. For details about file descriptions, see {\uldb 
Working with descriptions}{\v Descriptions}.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Show miniature versions of icons
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Turn this setting on to shrink large icons down to 16 x 16 when displaying small icons or list view (it only affects icon windows, not the {\uldb Bin}{\v Bin} or {\uldb Find Files dialog}{\v FindFiles}
).  This display mode is slow!
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Show folder/drive names for icon window captions
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 When this is turned on, icon windows display just the 8 letter directory name on icon windows, and root windows show the drive's caption from the Computer.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Do not show file extension for files with own icon
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
Calmira compares each icon to the blank file icon before writing the caption.  If this option is on, and the icon is not the blank file icon, then the 3 letter extension is truncated.  This feature is useful for reducing clutter, but if more than one file
 type uses the same icon (e.g. both GIF and JPG types use a graphics icon), then you won't be able to distinguish between files with the same 8 letter name.
\par \pard \s21 
\par 
\par \pard\plain \s18\keepn \b\f5\cf2\lang2057 \page {\cs15\f6\fs16\up6 #{\footnote \pard\plain \s16 \f6\fs20\lang2057 {\cs15\fs16\up6 #} FindFiles}} {\cs15\f6\fs16\up6 ${\footnote \pard\plain \s16 \f6\fs20\lang2057 {\cs15\fs16\up6 $} Find Files dialog}} {
