\f6\fs20\lang2057 {\cs15\fs16\up6 +} 00000}} Find Files dialog
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
\par This dialog lets you rapidly search for files in the background.  You can open it from the {\uldb Start Menu}{\v StartMenu}, desktop popup menu, {\uldb Computer}{\v computer} window or {\uldb icon windows}{\v IconWindows}.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Searching for files
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
To look for multiple sets of files, separate each wildcard with a semi-colon.  When you press the Search button, the search takes place in the background and you can carry on with other tasks.  The cursor changes to a pointer with an hourglass 
attached, and returns to normal when the search is complete.  Files and folders are displayed in the listbox as soon as they are found.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Searching for substrings
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
If you search for a file string that does not contain a dot, Calmira will return all the filenames containing that string at any position.  For example, if you search for "win", you might receive win.com,windows, win.ini and config.win.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Opening an item
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Double click on an item to open it, or right click on the listbox to display commands that let y
ou open an item's parent folder or delete it.  Ctrl and Shift can be used to select multiple items, and they can be dropped into other programs.  To open a file using a specific program, right click and choose {\uldb Open With}{\v OpenWith}.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 The search speed
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Calmira tries to ensure that there are no duplicates in the listbox.  You can gain maximum search speed if you specify only one wildcard for each search {\i and} clear the listbox between searches.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 {\b\cf2 Tip:} to search an entire drive, just enter a single drive letter in the {\i Start From} box.
\par \pard \s21 
\par 
\par \pard\plain \s18\keepn \b\f5\cf2\lang2057 \page {\cs15\f6\fs16\up6 #{\footnote \pard\plain \s16 \f6\fs20\lang2057 {\cs15\fs16\up6 #} RunProgram}} {\cs15\f6\fs16\up6 ${\footnote \pard\plain \s16 \f6\fs20\lang2057 {\cs15\fs16\up6 $} Run Program dialog}} {
\cs15\f6\fs16\up6 K{\footnote \pard\plain \s16 \f6\fs20\lang2057 {\cs15\fs16\up6 K} run program dialog; running programs; launching programs; programs; folders; opening folders; documents; DOS commands; dialog boxes; MS-DOS}} {\cs15\f6\fs16\up6 +
{\footnote \pard\plain \s16 \f6\fs20\lang2057 {\cs15\fs16\up6 +} 00000}} Run Program dialog
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
\par This dialog lets you start a Windows or MS-DOS program, or execute an MS-DOS command.  You can open it from the {\uldb Start Menu}{\v StartMenu}, desktop menu, {\uldb Computer}{\v Computer} window or {\uldb icon windows}{\v IconWindows}.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 If you check the DOS command{\b  }check box, the text you type in is passed to your command interpreter so you can obtain directory listings etc... Otherwise, the text is passed to Windows to execute.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 If you check the DOS session check box, windows will temporarely sh
ut down, exucute the program, and restart windows after the program has completed. This is usefull for DOS programs that require the full DOS environment to be available, ie. games and other graphic based DOS programs.
\par \pard \s21 
