\pard\plain \s16 \f6\fs20\lang2057 {\cs15\fs16\up6 +} 00000}} Open With dialog
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
\par \pard \s21 This dialog lets you open a file with a particular program.  Select a file in an icon window, right click over it and choose Open With from the popup menu.  Type the name of a program into the edit box and press OK.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 You can also choose a program from the listbox by double clicking on an item.  If you single click instead, the program's details appear in the edit box and you can edit the command before pressing OK.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Adding programs to the dialog
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 The [File Viewers] section of the INI file lets you add entries to the listbox.  Each line should be in the format <caption>=<command>. For example:
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s20 \f11\fs18\cf1\lang2057 [File Viewers]
\par \pard \s20 Notepad=c:\\windows\\notepad.exe
\par Write=c:\\windows\\write.exe
\par Pif Editor=c:\\windows\\pifedit.exe
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
\par \pard \s21 You can include parameters within the command lines, and if you need to place the name of the document file at a specific point, insert the environment string %filename% at the required position.  For example:
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s20 \f11\fs18\cf1\lang2057 viewer.exe %filename% /p
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
\par \pard \s21 
