\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 {\*\bkmkstart Troubleshooting}{\*\bkmkend Troubleshooting}
\par This section contains a list of more frequent problems and their possible remedies.  You can also find useful information in the {\uldb Questions and Answers}{\v QandA} section.
\par \pard \s21 
\par 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 "Out of resources" error when Program Manager shows plenty
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 See the Video Driver Incompatibilities section below
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Icons disappear randomly and/or Start Menu is partially visible
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 This is a known problem caused by Adobe Type Manager (ATM).  If you are using ATM 2.0 or 2.5, manually edit your System.ini file and comment out the following two lines by adding semi-colons in front of them:
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s20 \f11\fs18\cf1\lang2057 system.drv=atmsys.drv
\par \pard \s20 atm.system.drv=system.drv
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
\par \pard \s21 
Contact Adobe to receive the latest drivers.  If you are using ATM 3.0 or higher, add the setting ATMIcon=off to the [Settings] section of Atm.ini.  This should allow Calmira to be displayed correctly, but there will be no ATM icon at the bottom-left of t
he screen.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 You should see the Video Driver Incompatibilities section below.  Sometimes, this problem does not occur if you run Calmira as an ordinary application, using Program Manager as the shell.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Calmira doesn't run as the Windows shell
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 If you get the error message "Cannot run progman" or a similar one, check that you've included the full pathname of Calmira in the shell= line.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 
You can run Windows by typing WIN /B at the DOS prompt, which creates the Bootlog.txt file in the Windows directory.  Look at the last few entries in the file.  If Calmira fails to load due to "return code 3", try moving all the Calmira files into the Win
dows directory and editing the shell= line again.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 If a driver or DLL has failed to load, Calmira may be incompatible with that file for some reason; there have been reports that replacing the file with a different version may solve the problem.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Program Manager loads even when Calmira is the shell
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 You can check whether Calmira really is the shell by opening the Shutdown dialog from the {\uldb Start Menu}{\v StartMenu}
 -- the Quit Calmira option is disabled when this is the case.  If so, make sure Program Manager is not being loaded from elsewhere, such as the Load= and Run= lines of Win.ini, the Startup menu, or another utility.  If the Quit Calmira option {\i is}
 enabled, then your System.ini may contain another shell= line above the one specifying Calmira.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Wallpaper palette is not restored correctly
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
This is a known problem on 256 colour displays when Calmira is used with some programs that require an extended palette, i.e., more than just the 20 system colours reserved by Windows.  It also occurs with other programs when Calmira is not running.  The 
effect can be minimised if you use a 16 colour wallpaper, or you can use the Repaint Screen command from the desktop menu when required.
\par 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Keyboard shortcuts don't work
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Make sure you have specified the {\uldb key combinations}{\v KeyboardShortcuts}
 correctly -- you need to add two or more keys from the set (Ctrl, Alt, Shift).  If you only specify Ctrl+A, for example, Calmira ignores the setting.  Also check that the caption you entered still exactly matches the {\uldb shortcut}{\v References} or {
\uldb Start Menu}{\v StartMenu} item's caption.  For menu items, remember to include the ampersands (&) and any menu-break specifiers like *2.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 You may need to disable other utilities which monitor the keyboard for special key combinations, although Calmira should work with well-behaved utilities like QuicKeys from Microsoft.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Programs can't find files in their home directory
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Some programs need to be started from their home directory so that they can find INI files and other special files.  If you receive "Cannot find file" errors, you should use their home directory as the 
Working Folder field when creating shortcuts, aliases or Start Menu items.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 "Stream read error" when opening an icon window
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 This could occur if Calmira tries to interpret a normal file as an {\uldb alias}{\v References}
.  By default, Calmira assumes that all files with an extension of ALS are alias files.  If there is a problem with this, you can move non-alias ALS files into a separate folder, or change the alias extension which Calmira uses (see {\uldb 
Miscellaneous Settings}{\v MiscSettings}).
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Text and labels are mis-aligned
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Calmira was designed using small screen fonts, and some of the windows and dialog boxes may look untidy when used with large fonts.  You can try changing some of the fonts by editing the INI file (see {\uldb 
Miscellaneous Settings}{\v MiscSettings}), otherwise, there is nothing you can do to improve the display except run Windows setup and choose a video driver that uses small fonts.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 General Protection Fault in module VDOACM16.DLL
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Calmira may not be compatible with this file, so if you encounter the above message, you need to disable the piece of software that is using it.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Programs crash when used with Calmira {\i or}
\par \pard \s19\sa30 Calmira crashes when used with another program
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Serious problems should rarely occur, but if they do, the most likely culprit is the Taskbar, because it interacts with other programs in unusual ways, such as resizing and moving their windows.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 You can turn off these settings in the Taskbar Properties dialog to try and find the exact feature which is causing the problem:
\par \pard \s21 
\par \{bmc bullet.bmp\} Keep Taskbar on screen all the time
\par \{bmc bullet.bmp\} Fit maximised windows to space above Taskbar
\par \{bmc bullet.bmp\} Move minimized window icons above the bar
\par \{bmc bullet.bmp\} Hide the icons of minimized applications
\par 
\par \pard \s21 To stop the Taskbar from intercepting mouse messages, add the line UseMouseHook=0 to the [Taskbar] section of Calmira.ini.  This may avoid some conflicts, but then the Taskbar won't be able to hide itself automatically.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 Please read the {\uldb General Troubleshooting}{\v Trouble} section for more help.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Some Program Manager groups are not imported into the Start Menu
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
On some computers, not all of the groups or items get imported in the Program Group Convert dialog.  This seems to be dependent on Program Manager or the DDE interfacing, since problematic group files can successfully be converted on another computer.  Th
ere is no known solution at present.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 "Access denied" message when copying or moving a file
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Check that the file has not been opened by another application which is still running, e.g. you need to close Microsoft Word documents before they can be copied.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Cursor flickers or disappears when dragging across the desktop
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Turn off the Animate Cursor setting in the {\uldb Desktop Properties dialog}{\v DesktopProp}.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 New programs don't appear immediately on the Taskbar
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
Calmira doesn't show a button for a window until it has received an Activate message, which is sometimes lost or not sent.  Click on a different window, and click on the new application again to allow the Taskbar to detect the new program.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Small icons always appear faint
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 This could be due to the different ways that video drivers shrink bitmaps.  You can try setting the darker stretch modes in the {\uldb Start Menu Properties}{\v StartMenuProp} and {\uldb Taskbar Properties}{\v 
TaskbarProp} dialogs, but you may need to change your video driver to get better results.  See the screenshots in this help file for an example of roughly what the icons {\i should} look like.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Start Menu and Taskbar graphics suddenly change colour
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Some programs which use an extended 256 colour palette can inadvertently modify the palette used by Calmira's bitmaps, replacing one colour with another.  You need to rebuild the {\uldb Start Menu}{\v StartMenu}
 or Calmira itself to restore the bitmaps' palettes.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Video driver incompatibilities
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Calmira may not work correctly with some video drivers that use more than 256 colours, or video drivers which are too old or badly written. Symptoms may include:
\par \pard \s21 
\par \{bmc bullet.bmp\} "Out of resources" errors when resources are not low
\par \{bmc bullet.bmp\} Disappearing icons in various windows
\par \{bmc bullet.bmp\} A partially visible Start Menu
\par \{bmc bullet.bmp\} Start Menu icons becoming random pixels
\par 
\par \pard \s21 
You should install the standard 640x480 16 colour VGA driver from Microsoft to test if the problem lies in the video driver.  If so, contact your graphics card manufacturer for a driver update, or use generic 256 colour Super VGA drivers from Microsoft, w
hich are highly recommended.  They are often supplied on CD-ROMs from magazines, or you can download them from {\cf9 ftp.microsoft.com}.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 High-end video cards may also cause some of these symptoms if they perform various graphics optimisations.  You can try turning off the optimisations from the video driver's configuration program.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 URLs are not opened by web browser
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
For Calmira's Internet features to work, you need a web browser that supports the standard DDE interface defined by Spyglass Inc.  This includes Netscape Navigator 2.0 and up and Microsoft Internet Explorer 3.0 and up.  Netscape Communicator users, see th
e {\uldb Internet}{\v Internet} topic for help.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 Sometimes repeating an action (e.g. clicki
ng on a shortcut) should open the URL correctly.  You may also experience problems if your browser takes too long to load, causing the DDE system to time-out.  This may simply have no effect, or you may receive error messages, in which case, you must laun
ch the browser using the command line setting.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 WinZip says "Incompatible Program Manager replacement"
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Some setup programs query Program Manager for information about current program groups and items, but due to a technology limitation, Calmira does not return information about the Start Menu to other programs.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 
If you receive an error message saying that there is an incompatible Program Manager replacement, you need to turn off the option that lets install programs modify the menu.  When you do this, Program Manager will be loaded every time you install somethin
g.
\par \pard \s21 
