\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 MS-DOS programs do not show the correct icon in Alt+Tab
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 This feature requires a particular shell DDE service for MS-DOS programs which Calmira does not implement.  Graphics mode is used most of the time, and the {\uldb Taskbar}{\v Taskbar}
 shows your chosen icons for MS-DOS programs.  The Taskbar goes further than the shell DDE because it can show a different icon for each instance of a program, whether it is MS-DOS or Windows.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Install programs cannot retrieve Start Menu information
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 When Calmira is the shell, installation programs can add items to the Start Menu but cannot obtain information about the submenus and menu items.  This is because Calmira does not respond to the DDE command t
hat requests program group information, and a future version may implement this feature.  If an installation program does not work correctly, turn off the install feature in the Start Menu Properties dialog.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Icon windows can show the same file or folder multiple times
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 The wildcards used in file filters for {\uldb icon windows}{\v IconWindows}
 must be mutually exclusive.  For example, *.exe and *.com are mutually exclusive because a file cannot have both an EXE and COM extension.  If the filters overlap, you will end up with duplicate files, probably resulting in errors.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Taskbar icons are different when the Taskbar is reloaded
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
Some icons for the Taskbar are obtained directly from Calmira when programs are launched.  This includes programs that are started from shortcuts, aliases or the Start Menu, and the Taskbar does not retrieve the same icons if you unload the module and run
 it again.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Word for Windows 2.0 runs WinHelp if you click on the maximized caption
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 This is a side effect of preventing maximized windows from being moved.
\par 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 New file associations do not change document icons
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 When you associate a file through the {\uldb File Properties dialog}{\v FileProp}
, there will be no effect on the icons displayed until you restart Calmira.  However, the correct program will be launched when you double click on a document.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Extended ASCII filename characters not raised or lowered properly
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 If you create filenames using accented characters, these will not be displayed properly in Calmira because accented upper case characters are not converted
 to the correct lower case equivalents.  The underlying MS-DOS file system may or may not distinguish the filenames converted byCalmira; do not use Calmira to modify these files if you are in doubt.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Popup hints do not show descriptions in Small Icons view
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 The hints only work as expected in the Large Icons view.  To show descriptions with small icons, you need to use the List view and enable the description column.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Shortcuts can be re-arranged by Task Manager and other programs
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 All of Calmira's icons on the desktop are implemented as ordinary minimized windows, so it is possible for programs such as the Task Manager to move the icons to the bottom of the screen as if they were applications.

\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 
If this happens, you can use the Restore Shortcuts command on the desktop menu, which moves the shortcut icons back to their last saved position. Calmira's own icon arrangement commands accessed from the desktop menu will not disturb the placement of shor
tcuts.  Also, Calmira's own task manager will respect shortcut placement.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Pixels on Start Menu icons are turned blue by the highlight bar
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 The {\uldb Start Menu}{\v StartMenu}
 uses bitmaps instead of icons.  Bitmaps use less memory because they don't have a transparency mask, and the drawback is that they can only use simulated transparency by replacing all pixels of one colour (silver in this case) with another colour (the bl
ue from the highlight).
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 The Taskbar is not hidden when the cursor moves over a scroll bar
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 The {\uldb Taskbar}{\v Taskbar} only detects mouse movements over the client area of windows, which does not include window frames or scroll bars.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Icon windows do not refresh automatically like File Manager
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Calmira does not detect notification messages about changes in the file system.  You must refresh {\uldb icon windows}{\v IconWindows} manually when some files have changed.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Filters, column choices and icon view modes are not saved
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Icon windows are always opened with the settings from the {\uldb File System Properties dialog}{\v FileSystemProp}, even when their screen positions are saved.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Calmira's keyboard and mouse features do not work with some Win32s programs
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Calmira is a 16-bit Windows program, and the windows hooks, which it uses to detect messages being sent, are not triggered by some 32-bit programs (ie. winhlp32.exe) because they run in a slightly different environment.

\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Hot-key assignments are activated when using Alt Gr
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 The Alt Gr key generates the same key combination as Ctrl+Alt.  Do not assign a command to Ctrl+Alt+<key> if you normally use Alt Gr+<key> to enter a special character.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Files cannot be binned from the Find Files dialog
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 The {\uldb Bin}{\v Bin} only accepts files and folders from icon windows.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Icons "drawn" by programs are not reflected in Taskbar buttons
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Some programs paint their own minimised icons instead of specifying a fixed icon to use. There is no easy way to intercept this.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Microsoft Telnet crashes when run alongside Calmira
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 The Alt key activates Calmira windows and flashes the title bar
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 When you press the Alt key from one of Calmira's windows, all of the windows are brought to the front.  Also, the title bar of the active window flashes briefly when Alt is released.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 The cursor is not released after right clicking during certain drags
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 You should not right click while dragging files from the {\uldb Find Files dialog}{\v FindFiles} or {\uldb Bin}{\v Bin}
.  These windows use list boxes, and Calmira is unable to detect that files are being dragged.  The problem does {\i not} affect icon windows, where right clicking during a drag operation is essential for copying/moving files.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Association tab page displays blank registry entries
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Some registry entries which are incorrect can cause the combo box on the Association page of the {\uldb File Properties dialog}{\v FileProp}
 to display just "(No command specified)" lines with no file type description.  Do not associate files with these entries.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Limitation on reported disk and file sizes
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 The largest whole number that Calmira can store is 2,147,483,647 which is equivalent to 2GB, so any disks or file systems that are larger than this will not have their sizes correctly reported.  Usually, sizes l
arger than 2GB will simply be reported as 2GB.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Menu separators can become parent items
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 You should not put a minus sign in front of parent menu captions, because they will be drawn as separator lines.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Menu separators can be "selected" using cursor keys
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 The separators of a 3D Start Menu are implemented as real menu items because normal separators cannot have a 3D effect.  The highlight bar will disappear when it moves over such items.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Adobe windows can't be closed with right click
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 You may receive a general protection fault if you attempt to close a window by right clicking on the minimize or maximize box of Abobe programs such as Acrobat Reader and Photoshop.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Folder names must not contain trailing spaces
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 When you use an "open folder" style command from anywhere within Calmira, make sure that there are no trailing spaces in the folder name.  For example "c:\\games" is OK, but "c:\\
games " may cause problems because MS-DOS can find the directory, but the contents will not be accessible when Calmira appends a filename to the latter path.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Shortcuts accidentally created when opening from the Computer
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
When you double click on an icon in the Computer, you should not move the cursor out of the window until the program has finished loading.  If you move the cursor over the desktop during the load, a shortcut may be created because the program start-up has
 interrupted mouse messages, and Calmira believes that you are still dragging.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Minimized icon windows still show a pressed taskbar button
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Some dialog boxes from other programs are truncated by the Taskbar
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Ampersand in menu captions
\par \pard\plain \f6\fs20\lang2057 {\f5 
To show "&" in a Start Menu caption, enter "&&" instead, otherwise the space after the "&" is treated as a keyboard mnemonic.  For the same reason, there is a problem with Calmira's message boxes, which display filenames containing the & character incorre
ctly as an underscore.
\par }\pard {\f5 
\par }\pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Progress bar colour must be silver
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 The progress bar background should be always be set to "silver" or "btnface", even though there is an option to change it.  This is because the new Win95-style gauge does not paint its background colour properly.
\par \pard \s21 
