\cs15\f6\fs16\up6 K{\footnote \pard\plain \s16 \f6\fs20\lang2057 {\cs15\fs16\up6 K} troubleshooting; bugs; reporting bugs; help}} {\cs15\f6\fs16\up6 +{\footnote \pard\plain \s16 \f6\fs20\lang2057 {\cs15\fs16\up6 +} 00000}} General Troubleshooting
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
\par \pard \s21 If you are experiencing any difficulties that are not covered above, you can follow these guidelines to try and isolate the cause.  You should exit to DOS and run Windows again after trying out a software modification.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Visit the web site for the latest information
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 If you have Internet access, you can view up-to-date information about any bugs or incompatibilities that are discovered.  Otherwise, you can receive all published documentation if you order a new version by post.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Read the relevant help topics again
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
Make sure that you are using Calmira correctly, and understand how to use the features.  Many "problems" are simply a misunderstanding of the way things work, or minor omissions such as forgetting to type the full pathname or the working directory. Consul
t your Windows and MS-DOS manuals where appropriate and check the Calmira Readme file too.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Find out how to repeat the problem
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 You need to be able to write down a list of steps that can reliably reproduce the problems. An investigation often produces useful information and patterns, and you certainly need it if you want to report a bug.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Try to reproduce the problem on another computer
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 This is usually a good way to determine whether the problem lies with Calmira.  If it runs fine on a friend's PC, then find out what the differences are, and adjust your software configuration to match the other machine.

\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 If the cause is an unusual program
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
Remember that Calmira should not be expected to work with every program on the Internet .  If you're having problems with utilities that perform special operations or tricks with graphics or the user interface, then the best solution is not to use the con
flicting programs at the same time.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Make sure there is enough memory and resources
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Calmira's behaviour is undefined if memory or resources are very low.  You may eventually get error messages, but before that happens, there may be strange effects on the s
creen such as areas not being fully repainted.  You can try and make more resources and memory available by following the guidelines in the {\uldb Optimising Calmira}{\v OptimisingCalmira} and {\uldb Optimising Windows}{\v OptimisingWindows} topics.

\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Run Calmira as a normal Windows program
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 If this improves the situation, then follow the instructions in Common Problems for resolving shell issues.  Calmira should behave almost identically when it is the shell, so if there {\i is}
 a difference, it could be due to other drivers or utilities being loaded in a different order.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Dealing with general protection faults
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
When you get a GPF message, note down the filename in which the fault occurred (which could be a DLL file).  If it's not Calmira, find out which program uses the file and stop running it or disable the specific feature that uses the file. Some of Calmira'
s non-standard operations, such as right clicking to close windows, do not work with all programs.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Unload all other applications except Program Manager
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Of course, this is not applicable if your problem is to do with another application program, but if it appears to be confined to Calmira alone, then you should not run anything else while testing.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Unload all third party utilities
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
This includes everything in your Program Manager Startup group and in Calmira's Startup menu.  Look in Win.ini for the Load= and Run= lines and comment them out if they are starting any programs. Also uninstall Type Manager and similar low-level utilities
.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 Conflicts are most likely to occur when other utilities perform similar function to Calmira such as installing hooks to detect the mouse and keyboard, and modifying the behaviour of the desktop.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Run automatically loaded utilities later on
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
If you have programs that are causing problems in the Load= and Run= lines in Win.ini, or items in the Startup menu, try starting them manually after Calmira has completely finished loading and is idle.  If this works, you could write a script file to lau
nch them manually in future.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Change your video driver to a simpler one
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
If you are using a third-party Super VGA driver, change to a generic Super VGA driver supplied by Microsoft, or the standard 640x480 VGA driver that is supplied with Windows.  Do not use more than 256 colours when testing for problems.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 If your graphics card comes with extra utilities, use them to turn off any special features that your graphics hardware might have, and then remove the utilities from memory (unless Windows does not work without them).
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Uninstall potentially unstable drivers
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Look in the D
rivers dialog of Control Panel.  If you've experienced any problems with some of the drivers before, then remove them.  Also unload plugins and other web browser related utilities, which are extremely prone to crashing.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Uninstall as many drivers and add-ons as possible
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
Sound and music drivers are unlikely tocause problems, but graphics, screen, and font related drivers often interfere, so they should be removed if you can re-install them easily.  Also disconnect network devices, and run Calmira from a loca
l machine's standard hard disk with the minimum Windows setup.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Install a fresh copy of Windows
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
If you encounter a serious incompatibility problem but you really can't determine the driver or configuration that is causing the trouble, install another copy of Windows in a different directory.  Calmira should run correctly on all fresh installations, 
unless Windows is not configured properly for your hardware.  Once you get it working, install additional drivers and utilities one by one.
\par \pard \s21 
