\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 How can I print a file from Calmira?
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Select the file in an icon window and press Ctrl+P.  Alternatively, drag the icon into Print Manager's {\i window or minimized icon}
 (not a shortcut, a file icon, or a button on the Taskbar).  The file must be registered with a program that can open and print it.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Can I change the picture on the Start button?
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Yes, look at the topic on {\uldb customising bitmaps}{\v CustomBitmaps}.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 What if I think I've found a bug?
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Before you report it, read through the sections on {\uldb Common Problems}{\v CommonProbs}, {\uldb Known Issues}{\v KnownIssues} and {\uldb General Troubleshooting}{\v Trouble}
.  The last contains guidelines on reporting bugs, and there are also some useful answers contained in the rest of the current topic.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Is Calmira going to become Shareware?
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 No, it will always be freeware. Shareware is not effective without a nag screen or some other limitation, and I don't want to trouble the people who really cannot afford it.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 However, Li-Hsin had to turn down a US$ 32,000 exclusive rights deal with a well known software company, in order to release Calmira 2.0 as free software.  So if you're doing okay financially, then a small donation would be greatly appreciated.

\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Can you add \{some feature\} to the next version?
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
If it could be useful to a large proportion of users, then it will be considered.  I usually rule out ideas that are beyond the scope of managing files, programs and tasks, and also those which are purely cosmetic features.  These include animations, cale
ndars, diaries, alarm clocks, wallpaper facilities, desktop themes, Win95 style title bars and menus, and file viewers (just to name a few).
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard \s21 
Good ideas will be considered by their level of demand, difficulty of implementation and resource requirements.  So the highest priority goes to features that are in high demand, quick to program, and don't use excessive memory or processing power.  Be pr
epared to justify your ideas in detail -- I may need a bit of convincing!
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Why is there no "popup" help in the dialog box graphics?
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 This was discovered to be rather unhelpful because people don't always click on all the inv
isible hotspots, and so they miss out on essential information.  All the text is now completely visible, and every help page can be accessed through the << and >> browse buttons.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Why is the Taskbar listed in Task Manager?
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 The taskbar's window is managed independently from the other windows in Calmira, and Task Manager considers this to be a separate task.  You can now use Calmira's own task manager instead.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Can setup programs add icons to the Start Menu?
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Yes, just turn on the option from the Start Menu Properties dialog and restart Calmira.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Why do some resources seem not to be released?
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Delphi\rquote 
s runtime caches certain resources to speed up access when they are needed again.  It is quite normal for resources to decrease permanently by a few percent after an operation, provided this does not happen every time the operation is repeated, e.g
., opening a dialog box. Almost all of your resources should be returned when you quit Calmira.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 How do I run programs automatically at startup?
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Open the Start Menu Properties dialog and create a sub-menu captioned "Startup".  The menu can be anywhere, at any level.  Inside this menu, put links to the program you want to load.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Can icon windows refresh themselves like File Manager?
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 No, File Manager is treated differently by Windows, and receives a special message from the operating system to notify about file changes.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Can I use 256 colour icons or bitmaps with Calmira?
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 No, Calmira does not support a 256-colour palette when drawing its graphics.  256-colour icons can sometime
s be loaded on certain combinations of video drivers and Hi-Colour or True colour video modes, but certainly not on 256-colour video modes.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Can I compress/edit/hack the executable files?
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
It is not recommended. Look in the sections on customising bitmaps and icons if you want to change the graphics.  Do not be surprised if Calmira doesn't work after you change the resources with a Shareware or freeware utility.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Does Calmira work under Windows NT 3.51?
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 No, it was never designed with Windows NT in mind.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Will there be a 32-bit version of Calmira?
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 No, the difference between the MS-DOS and Windows 95/NT file systems is too great for a quick port.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 What does the Taskbar animation option do?
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 It slides the Taskbar onto the screen rather than just making it appear.  You may need a slower computer to observe the effect!
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Should I upgrade to Windows 95 or stick with Windows 3.1 and Calmira?
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 I would advise that if you've got a Penium-class computer with 32 MB RAM or better, then you should upgrade to Windows 95 or you'll miss out on the all the benefits that a modern operating system brings.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Where does the name Calmira come from?
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 It was just made up.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 How long did it take to write Calmira?
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 It's impossible to provide a figure, since the program was not developed full-time.  The first code was written around November 1995.
\par \pard \s21 
