\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 How do I open an icon window's popup menu in List View mode?
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Right click on a blank area of the toolbar or statusbar.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Will Calmira work correctly after 1999?
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Yes, it can can handle dates after 2000.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Why do programs excluded from the taskbar show an icon?
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 Calmira assumes that you will eventually need to activate a minimized program that is normally visible, so it must either be accessible from the taskbar or the desktop. You need to use a third p
arty utility to hide program icons completely.
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 How can I use more space for showing descriptions?
\par \pard\plain \f6\fs20\lang2057 {\f5 
You can enlarge the grid size through System Properties for Large Icons view. In List mode, you can set the DescriptionWidth setting (see the help file index). For long descriptions, it may be best to use MS-DOS filenames for icon captions, and create a w
ide description column in List view.
\par }\pard {\f5 
\par }\pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Why is name sorting sometimes wrong in the List view?
\par \pard\plain \f6\fs20\lang2057 {\f5 If you use descriptions as icon captions, the sorting may appear t
o be wrong in the list view when you sort by "name". In Large Icons view, the captions are used for sorting, and this is maintained in the list view to prevent the icons from being re-ordered every time you change views. So the filename column may not be 
in order.
\par }\pard {\f5 
\par }\pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Can the Start Menu highlight follow the cursor movement?
\par \pard\plain \f6\fs20\lang2057 {\f5 No, the Start Menu is a normal Windows 3.1 menu which must follow the standard menu interacton style, i.e. you must hold down the mouse button to move the highlight bar.
\par }\pard {\f5 
\par }\pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Can I hide the Computer icon?
\par \pard\plain \f6\fs20\lang2057 {\f5 Yes, give it a zero length caption.
\par }\pard {\f5 
\par }\pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Can a Start Menu item be made to exit Windows immediately?
\par \pard\plain \f6\fs20\lang2057 {\f5 You can download a small utility that exits Windows without asking for confirmation, for example, "Bailout". Simply drop it into the Start Menu.
\par }\pard {\f5 
\par }\pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Why does the 'Unable to run program or view file' message appear?
\par \pard\plain \f6\fs20\lang2057 {\f5 If you activate a shortcut or Start Menu item, you could get this message even though the program runs normally. Check that the directory in the Working Folder field actually exists -- if Wind
ows can't find the working folder, it may return an error value even though it has successfully loaded the program in question.
\par }\pard {\f5 
\par }\pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Why can't my taskbar resize maximized windows?
\par \pard\plain \f6\fs20\lang2057 {\f5 
It's possible that you have another utility installed, which is interfering with the message hook that Calmira uses to detect window resizing. Look in the Troubleshooting sections of the help file to see if anything helps.
\par }\pard {\f5 
\par }\pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Why are program options spread across several property dialogs?
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 If every option in Calmira were to be accessed from one large dialog with tabs, there would be certain problems, including:
\par \pard \s21 
\par \{bmc bullet.bmp\} Opening and closing the dialog would take a very long time
\par \{bmc bullet.bmp\} A large amount of memory is consumed at once to create all the controls.
\par \{bmc bullet.bmp\} The resource heaps may be severely depleted by too many controls.
\par \{bmc bullet.bmp\} There would not be enough space to add new options.
\par 
\par \pard\plain \s19\sa30 \b\f5\fs20\cf1\lang2057 Why is the Control Panel menu missing some icons?
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 The Start Menu is hard-coded with a typical set of entries, and Calmira does not detect any extra icons in your own control panel.  You can add them by creating menu items that use the command:
\par \pard \s21 
\par \pard\plain \s20 \f11\fs18\cf1\lang2057 c:\\windows\\control.exe <source> <icon caption>
\par \pard\plain \s21 \f5\fs20\lang2057 
\par \pard \s21 <source> is the name of the CPL file that runs the applet, and <icon caption> is the text seen in the Control Panel window.
\par \pard \s21 
